Red Scare HysteriaThe real lessons for the left in the U.S. and especially for Sanders’ pro-working class campaign which Socialist Alternative has endorsed are much different.
The endlessly repeated allegation of rife anti-Semitism in the Labour Party is based on very little and most of that little is based on conflating criticism of Israeli policy with anti-Semitism.
The exception was the 2017 election when Corbyn put forward a bold platform and held mass rallies around the country to mobilize support.
In the liberal media and among a lot of the left, Brexit is portrayed as a racist, anti-immigrant vote which anticipated Trump’s election here.
There is no evidence that his platform was “too radical” for most working class or young people.